{"nodes": [{"id": "draft_journey_draft3_1_doc", "label": "Draft 3.1 (hierarchical diffusion formalized)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft3.1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Brainstem named, hierarchical diffusion as central mechanism, SpecialGeneralist, two-timescale Limbic Loop, first protected list."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft3_1_brainstem", "label": "Brainstem (small central controller)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft3.1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Small named controller (~5-10k transistors): computes scalar loss, broadcasts pulse-width + tri-state sign, manages clocks. Not a CPU, not a backprop engine; sets rhythm like a biological brainstem."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft3_1_hierarchical_diffusion", "label": "Hierarchical Diffusion Backprop", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft3.1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The attribution era's central mechanism: loss diffuses down five levels, each dividing its share among children by stored contribution, conserved to the scap. Self-similar; mirrors neuromodulator diffusion. The rule that carried magnitude but never direction and broke at scale."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft3_1_specialgeneralist", "label": "SpecialGeneralist (gated reuse)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft3.1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "G receives a context mask per Specialist call, gating which sub-network activates; one shared unit learns multiple functions without gradient collision. Structurally close to mixture-of-experts / GLU, arrived at independently."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft3_1_two_timescale_learning", "label": "Two-timescale learning (Cortex fast, Hippocampus slow)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft3.1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Same topology, differentiated by update cadence: Cortex every clock, Hippocampus every k clocks (consolidation), Commissure slower still + decay term. Independently re-derived complementary-learning-systems theory."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft3_1_loss_conservation", "label": "Loss conservation (additive invariant)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft3.1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Sum of children_shares = parent_loss at every level (H6); additive not probability-like, making a Lyapunov-style debuggable invariant. Threatened by compounding analog error across five levels."}], "edges": [{"source": "draft_journey_draft3_1_doc", "target": "draft_journey_draft3_0_doc", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.95, "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft3.1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft_journey_draft3_1_doc", "target": "draft_journey_draft3_1_brainstem", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft3.1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft_journey_draft3_1_doc", "target": "draft_journey_draft3_1_hierarchical_diffusion", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft3.1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft_journey_draft3_1_doc", "target": "draft_journey_draft3_1_specialgeneralist", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft3.